# Tablet Photo Frame — Project Rules
# These rules give a fresh AI session all the context needed to work on this project.

## Project Overview
Node.js/Express 5 + WebSocket slideshow server for a tablet photo frame.
- `server.js` — backend (Express 5, `ws` WebSocket, multer uploads, ffmpeg/ImageMagick processing)
- `public/slideshow.html` — full-screen slideshow frontend (~1650 lines)
- `public/manage.html` — media library management UI (~1900 lines)
- `package.json` — uses `yarn` (not npm); run `yarn install` after adding deps

## Infrastructure

### Production Server
- **Host:** `192.168.68.50`
- **User:** `root` (key-based auth, no password needed)
- **App directory:** `/opt/slideshow`
- **Process manager:** PM2, app name `slideshow`
- **Deploy command:** `ssh root@192.168.68.50 'cd /opt/slideshow && git pull origin main && pm2 restart slideshow'`
- **Note:** Server branch has no upstream tracking; always use `git pull origin main`

### Git Remote
- **GitHub:** `https://github.com/Tiimber/tablet-photo-frame.git`
- **Branch:** `main`
- **Push then deploy:** `git push && ssh root@192.168.68.50 'cd /opt/slideshow && git pull origin main && pm2 restart slideshow'`

### Local Media Source (for bulk operations)
- **Local photos/videos:** `/Users/robbintapper/Desktop/frame/`
- Used when generating posters or processing existing media locally before uploading

## Home Assistant Integration

### HA Server
- **URL:** `http://192.168.68.140:8123`
- **Config file on server:** `/opt/slideshow/ha_sync.json` (gitignored, contains long-lived token)
- **HA config file:** `/config/configuration.yaml` on the HA host

### HA Entity IDs (synced from slideshow config)
| Config key     | HA Entity ID                              | Type           |
|----------------|-------------------------------------------|----------------|
| `interval`     | `input_number.slideshow_interval`         | input_number   |
| `transition`   | `input_select.slideshow_transition`       | input_select   |
| `kenBurns`     | `input_boolean.slideshow_ken_burns`       | input_boolean  |
| `kenBurnsSpeed`| `input_select.slideshow_ken_burns_speed`  | input_select   |
| `order`        | `input_select.slideshow_order`            | input_select   |
| `fit`          | `input_select.slideshow_fit`              | input_select   |

### Reloading HA entities after configuration.yaml changes
```
ssh root@192.168.68.140 'curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8123/api/services/input_select/reload \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $(jq -r .token /opt/slideshow/ha_sync.json)" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json"'
```
(Also reload `input_number` and `input_boolean` if those change.)

## Server-Side File Layout (on production server)
```
/opt/slideshow/
  server.js
  public/
    slideshow.html
    manage.html
  photos/          # processed images (gitignored)
  videos/          # processed videos (gitignored)
  thumbs/          # image thumbnails (gitignored)
  posters/         # video first-frame JPEGs (gitignored)
  pending/         # upload queue (gitignored)
  config.json      # runtime config (gitignored)
  meta.json        # display names + dates (gitignored)
  ha_sync.json     # HA URL + token (gitignored)
  server.config.json  # server tuning (gitignored)
```

## Gitignored Files (exist on server, not in repo)
- `config.json` — slideshow settings (interval, transition, kenBurns, order, fit, kenBurnsSpeed)
- `meta.json` — per-file metadata (displayName, date)
- `ha_sync.json` — `{ "url": "http://192.168.68.140:8123", "token": "..." }`
- `server.config.json` — port, paths, processing limits
- `photos/`, `videos/`, `thumbs/`, `posters/`, `pending/`

## Key Architecture Notes

### WebSocket
- Server broadcasts JSON messages to all connected clients via `broadcast(msg)`
- Client reconnects automatically with exponential backoff
- Message types: `config`, `photos`, `queue`, `show_now`

### Media Processing Pipeline
- Upload → `pending/` → `processQueue()` → `photos/` or `videos/`
- Images: ImageMagick `convert` → resize to 1920px max, strip EXIF, JPEG
- Videos: ffmpeg → H.264/AAC MP4
- Posters: `generatePoster()` → ffmpeg `-frames:v 1 -q:v 2` → `posters/NAME.jpg`
- Thumbnails: ImageMagick → `thumbs/NAME.jpg` (300px)
- Dates extracted via ExifTool during image processing

### Static Routes
- `/photos/` → `./photos`
- `/videos/` → `./videos`
- `/thumbs/` → `./thumbs`
- `/posters/` → `./posters`

### Key API Endpoints
- `GET /api/photos` — list all media with name, date, type
- `GET /api/config` — current slideshow config
- `POST /api/config` — update config (also syncs to HA)
- `GET /api/photos/:filename/info` — size, date, displayName
- `GET /api/photos/:filename/poster` — video poster JPEG
- `DELETE /api/photos/:filename` — delete media + thumb + poster
- `GET /api/version` — `{ commit: "..." }` git hash

## Slideshow Frontend Key Variables & Functions

### State
- `isPaused` — boolean, true when slideshow is paused
- `timer` — setInterval handle for slide advancement
- `config` — current settings object
- `photos` — array of filenames in display order
- `queuePos` — current index in photos array
- `slotA`, `slotB` — the two `.slide` div elements (double-buffer)
- `currentGroup`, `currentIsDual`, `currentIsStack` — currently displayed slide info
- `dateCache` — `filename → 'YYYY-MM-DD'` map

### Key Functions
- `startTimer()` — starts/restarts the interval timer
- `resumeSlideshow()` — clears isPaused, removes .paused class, calls startTimer()
- `window.nextSlide()` — advance to next slide with transition
- `window.prevSlide()` — go to previous slide with transition
- `openSettings()` — pauses slideshow, builds info panels, starts 30s auto-close
- `closeSettings()` — closes overlay, resumes slideshow
- `buildInfoPanels()` — creates per-media info panels around settings panel
- `openManageModal(fn)` — opens manage modal for a specific file
- `connectWebSocket()` — connects WS with auto-reconnect

### Gesture System (public/slideshow.html ~line 1380)
- **Swipe left** (>50px horiz, more horiz than vert) → `nextSlide()`
- **Swipe right** → `prevSlide()`
- **Short tap** (<500ms, <10px movement) → `tapPause()` — toggle pause, 30s auto-resume
- **Long press** (≥500ms, <8px movement) → `openSettings()`
- Variables: `gestureStart`, `longPressTimer`, `tapPauseAutoResume`

### Settings Overlay Auto-Close
- `settingsAutoCloseTimer` — 30s timer, resets on any interaction inside overlay
- `resetSettingsAutoClose()` — resets countdown bar animation + timer
- CSS `#settings-countdown` — blue bar at bottom, shrinks over 30s via CSS animation

### Video Poster Overlay
- `.video-poster` — `position:absolute; inset:0; z-index:1` img overlay on video slides
- Fades out (`opacity:0`) when video fires `playing` event
- Used in: slide display, info panels, manage modal preview

## Available Transitions (TRANSITION_LIST in slideshow.html)
`crossfade`, `fade_black`, `slide_left`, `slide_right`, `slide_up`, `slide_down`,
`zoom_in`, `zoom_out`, `circle_iris`, `diagonal_wipe`, `clock_wipe`, `pixelate`,
`glitch`, `shatter`

(Removed: `barn_doors`, `paint_brush`, `ripple`, `mosaic`, `blinds`)

## Development Workflow
1. Edit files locally in `/Users/robbintapper/tablet-photo-frame`
2. `git add -A && git commit -m "..."` 
3. `git push && ssh root@192.168.68.50 'cd /opt/slideshow && git pull origin main && pm2 restart slideshow'`
4. No build step — plain HTML/JS/CSS served statically
5. No `npm install` needed unless `package.json` dependencies change

## Common Pitfalls
- **apply_diff line numbers drift** after large insertions — use `search_files` to find exact current line numbers before diffing
- **git pull on server** needs explicit branch: `git pull origin main` (no upstream tracking set)
- **Gitignored config files** on server must be edited via SSH, not via git
- **ffmpeg/ImageMagick** must be installed on server for media processing
- **posters/** directory is created automatically by server on startup (`fs.mkdirSync`)
- When adding new HA entities: update `configuration.yaml` on HA host AND reload the entity type via REST API
